openmeteo-sh (1.4.0-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Persistent config file support (~/.config/openmeteo/config).
  * New config subcommand: init, show, set, get, unset, path.
  * Config defaults for API key, location, output format, units, timezone.
  * Precedence: CLI flags > env vars > config file > built-in defaults.
  * New --human flag to override config-set output format.
  * Fix --human flag in help subcommand causing unknown topic error.
  * Updated completions (bash/zsh) with config and --human.

 -- Nikita Shkoda <lstpsche@gmail.com>  Thu, 13 Feb 2026 20:00:00 +0000

openmeteo-sh (1.3.0-1) stable; urgency=low

  * New --forecast-since=N argument: skip to day N of the forecast (1=today).
    Available for weather, ensemble, marine, air-quality, flood.
    Mutually exclusive with --start-date.
  * New help subcommand: 'openmeteo <cmd> help' for general help,
    'openmeteo <cmd> help --daily-params' for detailed variable reference.
    All commands support help; param topics available where applicable.
  * Format-aware help: help output respects --porcelain and --llm flags.
    Porcelain outputs name=description, LLM outputs TSV.
  * Updated completions (bash/zsh) with --forecast-since and help.
  * Updated README with new sections and examples.

 -- Nikita Shkoda <lstpsche@gmail.com>  Mon, 09 Feb 2026 23:30:00 +0000

openmeteo-sh (1.2.0-1) stable; urgency=low

  * New --llm output format: compact TSV output optimized for AI agents.
    Resolves weather codes to text, embeds units in headers, minimal tokens.
  * Updated porcelain format review (no changes needed, confirmed best practices).
  * Updated completions (bash/zsh) with --llm flag.

 -- Nikita Shkoda <lstpsche@gmail.com>  Mon, 09 Feb 2026 23:00:00 +0000

openmeteo-sh (1.1.0-1) stable; urgency=low

  * Add --daily / --hourly flags for selective forecast output.
  * Add --start-date / --end-date for custom date ranges.
  * Geocoding fallback when full country name is used instead of ISO code.
  * --verbose flag for debug output (resolved locations, request URLs).
  * APT repository support via GitHub Pages.

